Modifications from the upstream JSONBench source:
  - Page title and branding changed from JSONBench to PipeBench.
  - Removed "Scale" and "Flattening" selectors (not applicable to pipeline
    benchmarks).
  - Metric radio buttons changed from {Cold Run, Hot Run, Storage Size,
    Data Quality} to {Throughput, Correctness}.
  - Embedded `data` array replaced with fetches to `data/index.json` and
    per-case `data/<case>.json` files produced by `harness report`. The
    UI fetches the index, then issues one parallel request per case, and
    stitches the results into the same in-memory shape the original UI
    consumed.
  - Test selection is driven by the chosen metric (performance tests for
    Throughput, correctness tests for Correctness).

All other presentation logic — the summary geometric-mean ratio, cell
colorize() thresholds, bar gradients, light/dark themes, link styles,
URL hash selectors — is unchanged from the upstream source.
